                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9469</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the Navy Department on August 17,
                        1937</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1937-08-17">August 17, 1937</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Navy Department announced today that the Headquarters of the 2nd Brigade,
                    Fleet Marine Force, and the 6th Regiment, composed of approximately 1,200
                    Marines, will sail in the naval transport <hi rend="italic">Chaumont</hi>
                    accompanied by the light cruiser <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> from San
                    Diego, California, for Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Brigadier General John C. Beaumont, U. S. M. C., commanding the 2nd Brigade,
                    Fleet Marine Force, will be in command. (Attached is a list of officers to sail
                    in the <hi rend="italic">Chaumont</hi>).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
